This paper deals with learning from demonstrations for mobile manipulation tasks, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper involves learning models of both task goals and underlying actions, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also leverages a probabilistic framework based on Monte Carlo tree search, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning and planning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves processing visual information to understand the environment, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with controlling a robot to perform tasks, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY).
